						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Pre-breeding-for-diversification-of-primary-gene-pool-and-genetic-enhancement-of-grain-legumes2" title=" Pre-breeding for diversification of primary gene pool and genetic enhancement of grain legumes " alt="link"> Pre-breeding for diversification of primary gene pool and genetic enhancement of grain legumes </a></h2>

	
					<p>Scientists at ICRISAT looked into wild relatives of grain legumes in order to find and exploit traits providing enhanced levels of &nbsp;resistance/tolerance to multiple stresses. The exploitation of these traits for cultivar improvement is limited by cross-incompatibility &nbsp;barriers and linkage drags. The researchers show that pre-breeding provides a unique opportunity, through the introgression of desirable &nbsp;genes from wild germplasm into genetic backgrounds readily used by the breeders with minimum linkage drag, to overcome this. Pre-breeding activities using promising landraces, wild relatives, and popular cultivars have been initiated at ICRISAT to develop new gene &nbsp;pools in chickpea, pigeonpea, and groundnut.<a href="http://www.frontiersin.org/Plant_Genetics_and_Genomics/10.3389/fpls.2013.00309/full" target="_self">http://www.frontiersin.org/Plant_Genetics_and_Genomics/10.3389/fpls.2013.00309/full</a>(<i>Front. Plant Sci.,</i> 20/08/2013)</p>
							<p><span class="date">5/11/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Pre-breeding-for-diversification-of-primary-gene-pool-and-genetic-enhancement-of-grain-legumes2">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/CTA-Science-Technology-Online-SWOT-Survey" title="CTA Science &amp; Technology Online SWOT Survey" alt="link">CTA Science &amp; Technology Online SWOT Survey</a></h2>

	
					<p>Please share your views with us&nbsp;to&nbsp;help&nbsp;inform CTA’s future&nbsp;Science, technology and innovation (ST&amp;I)&nbsp;programme priorities.The CTA Science, Technology and Innovation Strategies Programme (ST&amp;I) was launched in 2003 with the overall objective of enhancing ACP agricultural performance and economic development “through increased investments in knowledge, ST&amp;I as an engine of growth”. The underlying concept was that the ACP scientific and academic communities must be able to inform and influence national policies and programmes, identify and set priorities and support developmental goals that are needed for addressing the complex challenges of ARD.&nbsp;In 2012, the ST&amp;I strategies programme was integrated into a new department, Policies, Markets and ICTs.CTA believes that it is now timely to seek your views&nbsp;for&nbsp;assisting the Centre in defining the future orientation&nbsp;and priorities in&nbsp;ST&amp;I. To that end CTA has commissioned this survey for&nbsp;determining the way forward. &nbsp;You are, therefore, kindly requested to complete the attached survey and submit it before close of&nbsp;business&nbsp;on Friday 8th November 2013. <b><a href="http://www.surveymonkey.com/s/CTASTISWOT" target="_blank">Go directly to the questionnaire form.&nbsp; </a></b>We thank you for your cooperation.</p>
							<p><span class="date">25/10/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/CTA-Science-Technology-Online-SWOT-Survey">Read more...</a>
